/* Shootings and killings */ Added Israeli acknowledgment of killing what it described as six Hamas and PIJ terrorists, some "under the guise of journalists". Incredibly, this fact was left out of our article up until now—an especially egregious omission given that all three of the previously cited sources prominently noted those claims. That said, I've added RS with more specificity on that aspect of the event than the already included sources.

/* Violations and deviations by Israel */ Added widely reported fact that Gazan civilians shot were inside the buffer zone created by the ceasefire agreement—thus in violation of the ceasefire's terms. Included reaction from Israeli and Hamas officials. Removed poorly sourced Wikivoice assertion that the killed civilians were "returning home"—the sole source was Turkish state media, which claimed they were "returning to their areas", while other sources reported they were probing the border.

As I explained a few days ago, almost all media sources report that Hamas is releasing "hostages" while Israel is releasing "prisoners". Hardly any media source refers to those released by Hamas as "prisoners." Therefore, I believe the term "prisoner exchange" is misleading. In addition, although the article linked to discusses prisoner exchanges, our article deals with different and specific exchange of hostages/prisoners that justifies the addition of the word to the link.
